  "selection_rationale": "**Logistic Regression** was selected as the final model based on a composite evaluation across multiple metrics.\n\n- **F1-Score**: 0.6184 \u2014 balances precision and recall for the minority churn class.\n- **Recall**: 0.7888 \u2014 the proportion of actual churners correctly identified.\n- **ROC-AUC**: 0.8396 \u2014 the model's ability to distinguish between churners and non-churners.\n- **Accuracy**: 0.7417 \u2014 overall correctness (note: can be misleading for imbalanced datasets).\n\nF1-score was the primary selection criterion because accuracy alone can overstate performance when churn is the minority class. A model that predicts 'No Churn' for everyone could achieve ~73% accuracy but miss all actual churners \u2014 which defeats the purpose of the tool.\n\nWhen two models scored within 0.02 of each other, the more interpretable model was preferred to support transparent decision-making.",
